THE THREE CHRISTIANITIES (Historical Substrate)

Christianity 1 — Jesus's. Mystic, interior, anti-institutional. The kingdom is within you. Clean the inside of the cup. Act directly, at personal cost, without institutional mediation. Almost nobody practices this. Those who do are absorbed, marginalized, or killed by the institution, then canonized posthumously as marketing assets.

Christianity 2 — Paul's. Theological, doctrinal, organizational. Faith versus works. Justification by belief. Church structure, elder authority, behavioral norms codified in letters. The mystic teaching converted into organizational firmware. Paul is the first literalizer — the interior experience becomes a doctrine about interior experience teachable without having the experience.

Christianity 3 — Constantine's. State religion, imperial apparatus, colonial power projection. Christianity 2 fused with the Roman Empire's distribution infrastructure. Everything after 313 CE. The Crusades, the Inquisition, colonial missions, residential schools, manifest destiny, prosperity gospel, the 81% evangelical vote. State worship baptized in the vocabulary of Christianity 1 while running the OS of Christianity 2 on the power architecture of empire.
